doctype html
html
  head
    title= title
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheets/style.css')
  body
    div
    a(href='/')
      img(src='images/BearClawLogo.png')
    a(href='login') Log In
    a(href='myrecipes') My Recipes
    a(href='publicrecipes') Public Recipes
    h1= title
    h2= 'Ingredients'
    ul 
    li 4 cups cooked shredded chicken
    li 1 4-ounce can diced green chiles drained
    li 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder
    li 1/2 teaspoon cumin
    li 1/4 teaspoon onion powder
    li 3 cups shredded monterey jack cheese, divided use  
    li 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese, divided use
    li 14 corn tortillas
    li 2 10-ounce cans mild green enchilada sauce
    li 1 cup sour cream
    li salt and pepper to taste
    li Optional: chopped fresh cilantro, diced tomatoes
    li cooking spray
    h2= 'Instructions'
    ol
    li Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Coat a 9"x13" pan with cooking spray.
    li In a medium bowl, mix together the monterey jack and cheddar cheeses.
    li In a large bowl, mix together the chicken, 1/2 of the cheese, green chiles, garlic powder, cumin, onion powder and salt and pepper to taste.
    li Stack the tortillas on a plate and wrap with a damp paper towel. Microwave for 1 minute until tortillas are warm and pliable.
    li Lay one of the tortillas on a flat surface and spread approximately 2 teaspoons of sour cream down the center of each tortilla. Add approximately 1/3 cup of the chicken mixture, then tightly roll up the tortilla and place it seam side down in the pan. 
    li Repeat the process with the remaining tortillas. 
    li Pour the enchilada sauce over the top of the pan, the top the enchiladas with the remaining cheese.
    li Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve, topped with chopped cilantro and tomatoes if desired.
  
 



